text.section:
For an ordinary policy of life insurance issued on the standard basis, excluding any disability and accidental death benefits in the policy, the applicable table for the minimum standard for the valuation of the policy is:
if the policy was issued before the operative date of § 16-308 of this article, the Commissioners 1941 Standard Ordinary Mortality Table;
if the policy was issued on or after the operative date of § 16-308 of this article but before the operative date of § 16-309 of this article:
the Commissioners 1958 Standard Ordinary Mortality Table; or
at the election of the insurer, the Commissioners 1958 Standard Ordinary Mortality Table, calculating all modified net premiums and present values referred to in this subtitle for any category of policies issued on female risks according to an age not more than 6 years younger than the actual age of the insured; and
if the policy was issued on or after the operative date of § 16-309 of this article:
the Commissioners 1980 Standard Ordinary Mortality Table or, at the election of the insurer for any one or more specified plans of life insurance, the Commissioners 1980 Standard Ordinary Mortality Table with Ten-Year Select Mortality Factors; or
any ordinary mortality table, adopted after 1980 by the National Association of Insurance Commissioners and approved by a regulation of the Commissioner for use in determining the minimum standard of valuation for the policy.

section.section:
For total and permanent disability benefits in or supplementary to an ordinary policy or contract, the applicable table for the minimum standard for the valuation of the policy or contract is:
if the policy or contract was issued on or before December 31, 1960, the Class (3) Disability Table (1926);
if the policy or contract was issued any time from January 1, 1961 to December 31, 1965, both inclusive:
the tables specified by item (i) of this paragraph; or
at the option of the insurer, the Class (3) Disability Table (1926); and
if the policy or contract was issued on or after January 1, 1966:
the tables of Period 2 disablement rates and the 1930 to 1950 termination rates of the 1952 Disability Study of the Society of Actuaries, with due regard to the type of benefit; or
any tables of disablement rates and termination rates adopted after 1980 by the National Association of Insurance Commissioners and approved by regulation of the Commissioner for use in determining the minimum standard of valuation for the policy or contract.

For accidental death benefits in or supplementary to a policy, the applicable table for the minimum standard for the valuation of the policy is:
if the policy was issued on or before December 31, 1960, the Intercompany Double Indemnity Mortality Table;
if the policy was issued any time from January 1, 1961 to December 31, 1965, both inclusive:
a table specified by item (i) of this paragraph; or
at the option of the insurer, the Intercompany Double Indemnity Mortality Table; and
if the policy was issued on or after January 1, 1966:
the 1959 Accidental Death Benefits Table; or
an accidental death benefits table adopted after 1980 by the National Association of Insurance Commissioners and approved by regulation of the Commissioner for use in determining the minimum standard of valuation for the policy.
